---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import LucideIcon from "../../components/LucideIcon.astro";

const lang = "en";
---

<Layout
  title="Coffee and Cacao - Pachatopia"
  description="Growing by learning from nature: Pachatopia coffee and cacao in transition toward regenerative agroforestry."
  lang={lang}
>
  <Header lang={lang} />
  <main>
    <!-- Hero Banner -->
    <section class="relative text-white py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0">
        <img src="/images/production-cafe.webp" alt="Pachatopia Coffee" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover" aria-hidden="true" />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-primary/80"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6 text-center relative z-10 max-w-4xl">
        <div class="section-kicker mx-auto mb-6 w-fit border-white/15 bg-white/10 text-white">
          <LucideIcon name="Coffee" class="h-4 w-4 text-golden" />
          Regenerative crops
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-heading font-bold mb-6">Pachatopia Coffee and Cacao</h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-white/90">Growing by learning from nature</p>
      </div>
      <svg class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full" viewBox="0 0 1440 80" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" preserveAspectRatio="none">
        <path d="M0 40C240 80 480 0 720 40C960 80 1200 0 1440 40V80H0V40Z" fill="white"/>
      </svg>
    </section>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        <p>In the mountains of San Carlos, Colombia, coffee and cacao are among the traditional crops that shape the landscape and rural life. At Pachatopia, these crops are at the heart of our transition toward more nature-friendly agriculture.</p>
        <p>Today, our plots include several thousand coffee trees, which constitute our main production, as well as a few dozen cacao trees cultivated in certain areas of the project. Some plantations were recently established, while others existed before our arrival.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transition & Learning -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-14">
        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">A transition toward more natural practices</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">When we took over certain plots, the crops had been managed for many years with chemical inputs. We chose to gradually stop these practices, eliminating biocides and heavy chemical products.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">Instead, we are developing more natural approaches: compost and organic matter, natural liquid preparations, tree planting, and crop diversification.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">This transition takes time. Like soils, trees also need to gradually readjust to a more natural system after years of chemical agriculture.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">Learning through observation</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Alongside the plots in transition, we planted a small cacao plot under an already-wooded area, on a former meadow. This cacao, grown under the protection of trees, today seems to develop more harmoniously than that planted in open fields.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">This observation confirms what many farmers and researchers have found: coffee and cacao are forest plants that naturally thrive within diversified ecosystems.</p>
        </article>

        <article>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">Toward agroforestry systems</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">These experiences encourage us to gradually transform our crops into regenerative agroforestry systems, where coffee and cacao trees grow within a rich and balanced ecosystem.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">We are working specifically on planting shade and biomass trees, covering soils with mulch and protective plants, and promoting biodiversity and natural soil fertility. Step by step, these plots evolve toward an agricultural model that seeks to produce while regenerating the land.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Coffee & Cacao Today -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 space-y-8">
        <div class="surface-card p-8">
          <div class="icon-chip h-12 w-12">
            <LucideIcon name="Coffee" class="h-6 w-6 text-earth" />
          </div>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">Our coffee today</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Coffee is currently Pachatopia's main production. By choosing our coffee, you directly support the transition to agroforestry, tree planting and soil regeneration, as well as the development of the project and local communities.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">Every cup of coffee contributes to building a more nature-friendly agricultural model.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="surface-card p-8">
          <div class="icon-chip h-12 w-12 bg-accent/10">
            <LucideIcon name="Bean" class="h-6 w-6 text-accent" />
          </div>
          <h2 class="mt-5 text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">Cacao: a developing crop</h2>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Cacao is also among the crops we are gradually developing in our agroforestry system. Some plots are in transition toward more natural practices, and others were recently planted under forest cover.</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">Our goal is to produce in the future a cacao grown within a living ecosystem, in harmony with the forest. The first productions will be available in the coming years.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="surface-card-muted p-8">
          <div class="section-kicker mb-4 w-fit">
            <LucideIcon name="Leaf" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" />
            Field insight
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-4">Nature is our best teacher</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Coffee trees, cacao under forest cover, and agroforestry plots all point us in the same direction: cultivate with the ecosystem, not against it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sponsor -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="surface-card p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-6">Sponsor a coffee tree</h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">At the heart of Pachatopia, coffee trees are part of a living ecosystem that we seek to regenerate. Each tree grows alongside shade trees, biomass trees, fruit trees, and ground cover plants that enrich and protect the soil.</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">By sponsoring a coffee tree, you directly contribute to supporting the transition toward agroforestry, planting trees and enriching biodiversity, and accompanying the development of the project and local communities.</p>
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">Each sponsorship contributes to the gradual transformation of our plots into more balanced and more nature-friendly agricultural systems.</p>
        <a href="/en/comment-participer/" class="button-primary">Learn more about sponsorship</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Charter -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <div class="section-kicker w-fit mx-auto mb-4">
            <LucideIcon name="Leaf" class="h-4 w-4 text-accent" />
            Shared principles
          </div>
          <h2 class="section-title text-3xl md:text-4xl">The Pachatopia Charter</h2>
          <div class="section-divider"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="surface-card p-6"><p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-primary">Regenerate the Earth.</strong> We work to restore soils, forests, and ecosystems.</p></div>
          <div class="surface-card p-6"><p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-primary">Cultivate cooperation.</strong> Sustainable projects are built collectively.</p></div>
          <div class="surface-card p-6"><p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-primary">Work for peace.</strong> Caring for the Earth and working together contributes to building more peaceful societies.</p></div>
          <div class="surface-card p-6"><p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-primary">Respect the living world.</strong> The Earth, water, air, and all forms of life deserve our respect.</p></div>
          <div class="surface-card p-6 md:col-span-2"><p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-primary">Pass on to future generations.</strong> Preserve the beauty and richness of the world for tomorrow. Together, let's bring life back.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why choose Pachatopia coffee -->
    <section class="py-20 bg-cream">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-10 text-center">Why choose Pachatopia coffee?</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-12">
          <div class="surface-card p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-3">Agriculture in transition</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Our coffee is grown without heavy chemical products, within a system that is gradually transitioning toward regenerative agroforestry. Each cup supports this evolution.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-3">A regeneration project</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Buying Pachatopia coffee means supporting a concrete project: planting trees, enriching biodiversity, regenerating soils, and building a model inspired by nature.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-3">A human project</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Our coffee supports the development of local communities, contributes to the local economy, and promotes cooperation and knowledge sharing.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="surface-card p-8">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-heading font-bold text-primary mb-3">A cup with meaning</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Grown in the mountains of Colombia, our coffee benefits from an ideal climate for its development. A coffee to discover, linked to a genuine project.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-center text-lg text-primary font-semibold italic mb-8">Every cup of coffee is a seed planted for the future.</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="/en/comment-participer/" class="button-primary">Discover our coffee</a>
          <a href="/en/comment-participer/" class="button-secondary">Sponsor a coffee tree</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer lang={lang} />
</Layout>
